1. (A ∩ B) ∪ C = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 9}
2. A ∩ (B ∪ C) = {1, 3, 5, 7, 9}
3. No, the results are not equal. This demonstrates that while in some cases the distributive property of union over intersection (or vice versa) might yield the same result, it is not generally true. It's coincidental for these specific sets.

